"Unpasteurised milk"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPineapple\u003C/strong\u003E is safe to consume during pregnancy and provides important nutrients including vitamin C, manganese and bromelain. While some cultural beliefs suggest pineapple should be avoided, there is no scientific evidence that it causes harm during pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options are unsafe during pregnancy:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERaw meat\u003C/strong\u003E carries risk of toxoplasmosis and other food-borne infections\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnimal liver\u003C/strong\u003E contains excessive vitamin A which can be teratogenic in high doses\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUnpasteurised milk\u003C/strong\u003E may contain harmful bacteria like \u003Cem\u003EListeria monocytogenes\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERed wine\u003C/strong\u003E contains alcohol which is a known teratogen and should be completely avoided during pregnancy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPregnant women should focus on a balanced diet while avoiding foods that carry risks of infection or contain harmful substances that could affect fetal development.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pregnant women should avoid raw/undercooked meats, liver, unpasteurised dairy products, and alcohol due to risks of infection and toxicity.","Fresh fruits like pineapple are safe to consume during pregnancy and provide important nutrients including vitamin C and minerals."],"references":["Taylor M, Galanis E. Food safety during pregnancy. Can Fam Physician. 2010 Aug;56(8):750-1. PMID: 20705876; PMCID: PMC2920771.","Beasant L, Ingram J, Emmett PM, Cade JE, Taylor CM. Adherence to the national guidance on foods 